<Author>mshplover
<Content>Good for the Price Visited Dallas over New Years and was able to get a room for $30 a night. The hotel was very good for the price. The location is right off the Highway and you have to access it by using a service road which could be a pain at times but overall wasn't bad. There really isn't places walking distance to go, but a short drive if you have a car. The rooms were large and comfortable, only had a problem with the shower draining but nothing major. If you plan on using a taxi you may have issues, it took about 45 minutes to get a taxi so be prepared for a headache but that has nothing to do with the hotel itself. Overall this a good hotel for the price. It was my first visit to Dallas and would likely stay here again If I return. 
